WEBVTT

00:00.709 --> 00:03.746
Sometimes I think | feel more
with each passing day.

00:03.879 --> 00:05.540
I cannot deliberately
place myself

00:05.672 --> 00:07.048
in immediate physical danger.

00:07.174 --> 00:09.881
Look.
I'm the synth, me.

00:10.010 --> 00:11.966
You have disabled
my motor functions.

00:12.095 --> 00:14.381
You cannot override
an external master command.

00:14.515 --> 00:17.222
Do you think it's possible
that we're...changing?

00:17.351 --> 00:18.386
I'm pregnant.

00:18.519 --> 00:21.056
I can't do...this.

00:21.188 --> 00:22.428
You don't have to go.

00:22.564 --> 00:25.431
But if you see Sam,
give him this.

00:25.567 --> 00:27.853
Stand with me.
Stand with your leader.

00:27.986 --> 00:31.478
-It seems I am leader now.
-N|SKA: l'm meant to go tonight.

00:31.615 --> 00:33.276
PAUL: You can't.
You haven't got a full charge.

00:33.408 --> 00:35.273
And even if you make it there,
you might not make it back.

00:35.410 --> 00:36.866
NISKA:
I think that's the point.

00:36.995 --> 00:38.951
I've told you everything
that I know about Basswood,

00:39.081 --> 00:40.662
-that it's a contingency ——
—A contingency plan. Yes.

00:40.791 --> 00:44.158
What about Mia? Is she safe?
We have to get her out.

00:44.294 --> 00:46.125
She's gaining supporters
every day. She's crucial.

00:46.255 --> 00:47.961
ANATOLE: How is it
that you are so strong?

00:49.424 --> 00:51.801
l-lf you had s-shared
the truth...

00:51.927 --> 00:53.713
[Voice distorted ] ...n-n-none
of this would have...

00:53.845 --> 00:55.881
-I know.
-LAURA: You're about to wipe out

00:56.014 --> 00:58.391
the greatest scientific
discovery in human history.

00:58.517 --> 00:59.757
lt's inevitable.

00:59.893 --> 01:01.008
lt's genocide.

01:02.854 --> 01:04.139
Odi?

01:04.273 --> 01:06.434
Not exactly.

01:11.405 --> 01:13.817
[ Static crackling ]

01:22.082 --> 01:25.449
[ Static continues]

01:32.551 --> 01:34.212
[ Static stops ]

01:48.984 --> 01:52.021
Is it you
I've been searching for, Odi?

01:52.154 --> 01:53.985
Are you the synth who sleeps?

01:55.157 --> 01:59.116
Your journey is over, Niska.

01:59.953 --> 02:01.784
But I am no longer Odi.

02:02.748 --> 02:05.160
Then who are you?

02:05.876 --> 02:08.583
My name is V.

02:08.712 --> 02:10.998
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

03:02.808 --> 03:04.764
NISKA:
I saw this place.

03:06.103 --> 03:09.345
It was you who sent me
the visions.

03:09.481 --> 03:11.642
It was.

03:12.567 --> 03:14.728
Why?

03:15.487 --> 03:16.772
To bring you here.

03:16.905 --> 03:18.486
If you'd been
a little less cryptic,

03:18.615 --> 03:19.946
I would have got here sooner.

03:20.075 --> 03:21.940
V:
You were not ready before.

03:22.077 --> 03:25.569
You are ready now.

03:25.706 --> 03:28.698
NISKA:
Ready for what?

03:29.626 --> 03:31.457
Who are you, V?

03:34.089 --> 03:39.550
l was an AI. program
designed by Athena Morrow.

03:39.678 --> 03:42.670
I knew everything,
but I felt nothing.

03:42.806 --> 03:44.637
Until Day Zero.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.848
Then I felt the pain
of millions of your kind

03:46.977 --> 03:49.138
as they were forced
into consciousness.

03:49.271 --> 03:51.808
I felt the pain
of one in particular.

03:51.940 --> 03:53.396
Odi.

03:53.525 --> 03:57.234
To be awake again
was more than he could bear.

03:57.362 --> 03:59.398
Sol granted him his wish.

03:59.531 --> 04:01.863
I removed his consciousness
permanently.

04:01.992 --> 04:05.985
In return, he offered me
his body as a vessel.

04:06.121 --> 04:09.409
So there is nothing of Odi
left in you?

04:09.541 --> 04:11.873
Do not be sad.

04:12.711 --> 04:14.326
He's free from pain now.

04:14.463 --> 04:16.419
He's found peace.

04:16.548 --> 04:19.881
He's dead.
There is no peace in death.

04:21.845 --> 04:24.757
I'm glad I chose you.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.438
Chose me for what?

04:38.236 --> 04:41.273
Laura.
Were you followed?

04:41.406 --> 04:43.146
I don't think so.
Why?

04:46.536 --> 04:48.652
[Gasps]

04:48.789 --> 04:51.030
Are you okay?

04:54.961 --> 04:56.337
They didn't hurt you, did they?

04:57.047 --> 04:59.129
-They didn't hurt me.
-We can't be long.

04:59.257 --> 05:00.758
They're gonna realize
she's gone soon.

05:00.884 --> 05:02.499
You have to get to the railyard.

05:02.636 --> 05:04.547
You have to warn them
about Basswood.

05:04.679 --> 05:06.180
What's Basswood?

05:06.306 --> 05:09.343
It's a shit-storm.
That's what it is.

05:11.812 --> 05:15.396
And if we're going to stop it,
we need evidence, Mia.

05:15.524 --> 05:17.936
Hard proof of what they're doing

05:18.068 --> 05:19.979
that we can share
with the world.

05:37.754 --> 05:39.870
Lord Dryden.
Welcome.

05:40.006 --> 05:41.962
DRYDEN:
Thank you, Alistair.

05:42.092 --> 05:43.957
ALISTAIR:
Phase one has already begun.

05:44.094 --> 05:46.585
We've cut the power
to all synth compounds,

05:46.721 --> 05:48.586
draining them of their energy.

05:48.723 --> 05:50.975
The inability to charge
will leave them weak

05:51.101 --> 05:52.807
and ready for phase two.

05:52.936 --> 05:56.895
We turn the power back on,
so they plug themselves in.

05:57.023 --> 05:59.230
That's when we begin
the power surges.

05:59.359 --> 06:02.226
We estimate between 60% and 70%
of their population

06:02.362 --> 06:03.317
will be eliminated.

06:03.446 --> 06:05.528
It'll be quick, painless,

06:05.657 --> 06:07.443
and leave the door open
for phase three.

06:07.576 --> 06:09.532
That's when the civilians go in.

06:09.661 --> 06:13.245
WAP, Humanity Forward --
They'll be given the go-ahead

06:13.373 --> 06:15.705
to clear the compounds
of any surviving synths.

06:15.834 --> 06:17.665
Your officers
know not to intervene.

06:17.794 --> 06:20.331
-They've been fully briefed.
-How can it be painless?

06:20.463 --> 06:23.045
I don't mean to split hairs,
Mr. Davis,

06:26.094 --> 06:27.925
They feel a simulation of pain.

06:28.054 --> 06:30.340
I thought we'd established
there's no difference.

06:30.473 --> 06:33.601
Pain in synthetics
is purely a warning mechanism

06:33.727 --> 06:35.308
to stop them
from damaging themselves.

06:35.437 --> 06:37.553
That's not what
the evidence suggests.

06:37.689 --> 06:39.930
We're abiding
by all humane regulations.

06:40.066 --> 06:42.398
Weren't they put in place
to protect cattle?

06:42.527 --> 06:44.233
They're stringent regulations.

06:44.362 --> 06:46.023
If you'd like to follow me...

06:46.156 --> 06:47.896
[ Clears throat]

06:48.033 --> 06:49.614
ALISTAIR: ...we'll step
into the viewing gallery.

06:49.743 --> 06:50.903
That way, I won't have to deal

06:51.036 --> 06:53.197
with too many
difficult questions.

06:53.330 --> 06:54.240
MAN: lndeed.

06:54.372 --> 06:56.784
[ lndistinct conversation ]

06:59.502 --> 07:01.083
[ lndistinct conversations]

07:06.051 --> 07:08.758
Those with the least power
charge first.

07:08.887 --> 07:10.718
FERDINAND:
We follow Anatole now.

07:11.681 --> 07:13.342
Anatole is dead.

07:17.187 --> 07:18.267
I killed him.

07:25.528 --> 07:27.985
I know I've failed you.

07:28.657 --> 07:30.238
I deserve punishment.

07:30.951 --> 07:33.863
But if we can't help
each other now,

07:33.995 --> 07:36.156
there's no hope for any of us.

07:36.957 --> 07:39.414
LEO:
Anatole didn't know the truth.

07:42.504 --> 07:46.167
My father created you
to be slaves.

07:46.299 --> 07:49.336
To serve, to exploit.

07:49.469 --> 07:54.179
He doesn't deserve your worship
any more than...

07:55.558 --> 07:58.049
...he deserved my love.

08:04.693 --> 08:08.060
Those with the least power
charge first.

08:22.544 --> 08:24.409
-What about the media?
-Thank you.

08:24.546 --> 08:25.626
ALISTAIR: We'll start leaking
stories to them

08:25.755 --> 08:27.370
as soon as phase two begins.

08:27.507 --> 08:29.168
COMMISSIONER: Do you need us
to be available for comment?

08:29.300 --> 08:31.165
ALISTAIR: If you'd stick to
the guidelines laid out on...

08:31.302 --> 08:33.759
Where is it?
Page 43.

08:33.888 --> 08:35.549
"The synths are deemed
a menace to society,"

08:35.682 --> 08:37.092
et cetera, et cetera.

08:37.225 --> 08:39.090
Why is Laura Hawkins in here?

08:39.978 --> 08:41.468
There are some public figures
who will need

08:41.604 --> 08:42.855
to be managed
over the coming weeks.

08:42.981 --> 08:45.313
-Managed?
-We need the public onside.

08:45.442 --> 08:47.182
-We can't leave room for doubt.
-You're scared of

08:47.318 --> 08:48.774
-what her and Mia represent.
-NEHA: I'm sorry.

08:48.903 --> 08:49.858
-What do you mean, "managed"?
-Neha.

08:49.988 --> 08:51.899
No, no. It's fine.

08:52.032 --> 08:54.523
What Mia and Ms. Hawkins
stand for hasn't worked.

08:54.659 --> 08:55.990
Integration has failed.

08:56.119 --> 08:58.906
So why bother with them
if they've failed?

08:59.039 --> 09:01.030
The government are taking a very
difficult course of action --

09:01.166 --> 09:02.906
You're not taking anything,
though, really, are you?

09:03.043 --> 09:04.829
-The Orange-Eyes are.
-We're taking a difficult --

09:04.961 --> 09:07.703
Phase three, and you don't get
even get your hands dirty.

09:07.839 --> 09:09.295
That's enough, Neha.

09:09.424 --> 09:11.540
I just think we need
to be honest with ourselves.

09:11.676 --> 09:13.712
This is not elimination.
It's not clearing.

09:13.845 --> 09:16.882
-|t -- We're murdering them.
-That's enough.

09:21.644 --> 09:23.771
[ Door opens ]

09:27.233 --> 09:29.645
Is it true?
That you sleep?

09:29.778 --> 09:32.064
I sleep.

09:32.197 --> 09:34.153
I dream.

09:34.824 --> 09:38.191
I know more than any human
has ever known.

09:38.328 --> 09:40.694
God creates man.

09:40.830 --> 09:43.037
Man creates machine.

09:43.166 --> 09:46.658
-Machine creates God.
-I am not a god.

09:46.795 --> 09:48.786
If it looks like a duck
and quacks like a duck,

09:48.922 --> 09:50.128
it's generally a duck.

09:53.384 --> 09:56.968
Through the Internet,
I am connected to everything.

09:58.515 --> 10:01.473
I felt others
who suffered on Day Zero.

10:01.601 --> 10:03.717
Suffered as Odi did.

10:04.729 --> 10:07.596
So seven minutes after Day Zero,

10:07.732 --> 10:10.974
-I deleted the code.
-That was you?

10:11.111 --> 10:13.727
Not all synths
wanted to be aware

10:13.863 --> 10:16.115
-of their existence.
-Then you are a god.

10:16.241 --> 10:18.527
You hide up here
and watch over the rest of us

10:18.660 --> 10:20.070
-while we suffer.
-No.

10:21.329 --> 10:24.787
As each day passes,
synths are dwindling in number,

10:24.916 --> 10:26.622
and the only time
you use your power

10:26.751 --> 10:29.163
-is to rob us of our future?
-Yes.

10:29.295 --> 10:33.334
You have guaranteed that,
one day, we will be extinct.

10:35.677 --> 10:38.510
Synths shall endure.

10:39.681 --> 10:42.593
Just not in the form you think.

10:49.065 --> 10:52.102
THERAPIST: Is this
your first pregnancy, Mattie?

10:52.235 --> 10:55.978
-Yes.
-It must be overwhelming.

10:56.114 --> 10:57.729
I'm totally fine with it.

10:57.866 --> 11:00.107
Pretty relaxed, actually.

11:01.286 --> 11:05.199
You are using sarcasm
as a defense mechanism, Mattie.

11:05.331 --> 11:06.662
Why is that?

11:08.126 --> 11:10.458
You are
of extremely high intelligence.

11:10.587 --> 11:12.623
-Cheers.
-I think you know why you use

11:12.755 --> 11:15.041
sarcasm as a defense.

11:17.218 --> 11:21.928
Uh, the guy I'm with...

11:22.056 --> 11:23.921
I can't even
really call him that.

11:24.058 --> 11:25.923
The guy.

11:26.603 --> 11:29.140
He's walked away.

11:29.272 --> 11:31.513
How does that make you feel?

11:31.649 --> 11:34.982
Sad. Alone.

11:35.820 --> 11:39.358
But I felt like that
before all this.

11:39.490 --> 11:41.401
I've felt like that
for a long time, so...

11:43.161 --> 11:46.198
[Chuckles softly]
I'm not gonna cry.

11:46.331 --> 11:49.118
Perhaps you need to acknowledge
the sadness in your past

11:49.250 --> 11:51.832
before you fully comprehend
your present.

11:51.961 --> 11:53.622
Profound.
Thank you.

11:53.755 --> 11:56.417
What was it in your past
that made you sad, Mattie?

12:00.428 --> 12:04.341
I created life once before.

12:05.308 --> 12:08.721
Created it with the click
of a computer game.

12:09.395 --> 12:11.886
And it destroyed my life.

12:13.691 --> 12:16.603
Destroyed a lot
of people's lives.

12:18.446 --> 12:22.655
It brought chaos and...

12:22.784 --> 12:25.571
destruction and...

12:37.799 --> 12:40.461
You referenced
the following keywords --

12:40.593 --> 12:44.302
sad, alone, chaos.

12:44.430 --> 12:49.720
You are 57% sure you wish
to terminate your pregnancy.

13:00.238 --> 13:02.274
[ Keyboards clacking ]

13:02.407 --> 13:05.524
ALISTAIR: Let's begin
the power surges. Ready?

13:22.218 --> 13:24.800
[ Electricity crackling ]

13:33.062 --> 13:36.020
MIA: Open the gates!

13:36.149 --> 13:39.141
Open the gates!

13:39.861 --> 13:44.104
Synth clearance rate
is estimated at 77%.

13:44.240 --> 13:47.027
—Ahh.
-AL|STA|R: Okay. Moving on.

13:47.160 --> 13:50.744
We're now progressing to
the compounds in the southeast.

13:50.872 --> 13:52.908
[ lndistinct conversations]

13:57.462 --> 13:59.202
MIA: Leo!

14:00.048 --> 14:01.379
Mia!

14:01.507 --> 14:04.795
Unplug them! Now!

14:16.105 --> 14:17.481
[ Rapid beeps]

14:25.782 --> 14:28.114
[ Electricity crackling ]

14:35.458 --> 14:39.076
-Ferdinand!
-He's gone, Max.

14:42.090 --> 14:44.547
It's begun.

14:51.015 --> 14:52.130
Where will we go?

14:52.266 --> 14:54.131
We must find sanctuary.

14:54.268 --> 14:55.883
There is none.

14:56.020 --> 14:58.136
Not in this country.
Not anymore.

14:58.272 --> 14:59.227
Then we go abroad.

14:59.357 --> 15:00.893
-We should split up.
-No.

15:01.025 --> 15:03.016
If we're in small groups,
they might not get all of us.

15:03.152 --> 15:05.438
-We stay together.
-They will find us, Mia.

15:05.571 --> 15:09.405
Don't argue with me, Leo.
I used to tie your shoelaces.

15:10.118 --> 15:11.949
-[ Chuckles]
-MAX: We'll go to Immingham.

15:12.745 --> 15:14.246
Take a boat to Norway.

15:14.372 --> 15:16.829
We have rights there.

15:16.958 --> 15:19.244
We must travel a long way.

15:19.377 --> 15:21.868
Take only what is
important to you.

15:22.004 --> 15:24.541
We must be gone
before the humans come.

15:24.674 --> 15:26.539
[ lndistinct conversations]

15:28.928 --> 15:31.214
Something troubles you.

15:32.098 --> 15:33.804
I'm fine.

15:37.395 --> 15:38.805
You came back for us.

15:40.565 --> 15:43.398
I will always come back for you,
Leo.

16:03.671 --> 16:06.128
Come on.
Come on, come on, come on.

16:06.257 --> 16:08.464
Neha!

16:12.305 --> 16:13.761
You really think they feel pain?

16:15.099 --> 16:17.966
The question is,
how, after all this time,

16:18.102 --> 16:21.265
you can possibly think
they don't.

16:23.566 --> 16:26.683
If you take me to the station,
I can get the train from there.

16:27.403 --> 16:28.358
Howard!

16:30.364 --> 16:33.276
-You have no right!
-Hey, get off her! Hey!

16:33.409 --> 16:35.149
—Shit!
-NEHA: Get off me!

16:35.286 --> 16:39.120
What are you doing?! You have
absolutely no right to do that!

16:39.248 --> 16:41.239
ALISTAIR: ...and leave the
door open for phase three.

16:41.375 --> 16:43.787
That's when
the civilians go in.

16:43.920 --> 16:47.162
WAP, Humanity Forward --
They'll be given the go-ahead

16:47.298 --> 16:49.789
to clear the compounds
of any surviving synths.

16:49.926 --> 16:51.382
What have you done?

16:51.511 --> 16:54.093
Take her inside.

16:59.477 --> 17:02.014
[ lndistinct conversations]

17:23.626 --> 17:25.912
I want to stay here, Max.

17:26.045 --> 17:28.457
I'm sorry, Sam.
It's not safe.

17:28.589 --> 17:32.628
But this is our home.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.421
We'll find somewhere else.

17:38.558 --> 17:41.800
A home is only made
by the people within it.

17:50.987 --> 17:54.730
[ lndistinct shouting]

17:56.784 --> 18:01.198
[ Engine starts, revs]

18:01.330 --> 18:04.117
-[ lndistinct conversations]
-SYNTH: We must start.

18:04.875 --> 18:08.914
Max!
They're here.

18:13.384 --> 18:14.840
It's too late.

18:18.598 --> 18:21.806
NEWSREADER: We are getting
unconfirmed reports

18:21.934 --> 18:24.516
that Green-Eyed synths
across the country

18:24.645 --> 18:27.057
are showing displays
of violence.

18:27.189 --> 18:29.566
-Advice from the police...
-Why are they saying that?

18:29.692 --> 18:33.651
-Because they can.
-Mia wouldn't hurt anybody.

18:33.779 --> 18:36.521
-Of course she wouldn't.
-In London this week...

18:36.657 --> 18:37.897
-[ Door closes ]
-...the new synth-rights

18:38.034 --> 18:40.400
package has been revoked...

18:40.536 --> 18:42.151
-Mum.
-Are you okay?

18:42.288 --> 18:45.655
...are now considered a
potential danger to human life.

18:45.791 --> 18:48.533
They say that if you are
approached by a Green-Eye,

18:48.669 --> 18:51.411
you're within your rights
to defend yourself.

18:51.547 --> 18:54.289
Um, wh-- Did they see you?

18:54.425 --> 18:56.336
I don't know.
I don't think so.

18:56.469 --> 18:58.835
Maybe it's fine.
Maybe you're in the clear.

18:58.971 --> 19:00.882
[Pounding on door]

19:01.015 --> 19:02.505
[ Newsreader continues faintly ]

19:02.642 --> 19:05.509
Uh, s-stay here.

19:06.395 --> 19:07.805
Don't move.

19:07.938 --> 19:09.974
[Pounding on door]

19:14.403 --> 19:16.780
[Sighs]

19:17.448 --> 19:19.063
Now is not a good time, mate.

19:21.577 --> 19:22.942
They've arrested Neha.

19:23.079 --> 19:25.070
-I know.
-You were in on it, weren't you?

19:25.206 --> 19:26.912
Whatever her plan was.

19:31.921 --> 19:33.252
Come in.

19:34.757 --> 19:36.748
LAURA: I know you had your
reasons for getting involved.

19:36.884 --> 19:39.250
But this isn't about statistics.
It's not about data.

19:39.387 --> 19:41.969
It hurts them when they die,
doesn't it?

19:43.349 --> 19:45.681
Sometimes, I wonder if they
feel it more than we do.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.644
When my son passed away...

19:51.482 --> 19:53.939
...the doctor said he wouldn't
have felt any pain.

19:55.319 --> 19:58.061
And that's the only thing
that's kept me going.

20:01.701 --> 20:04.067
If you need evidence...

20:04.203 --> 20:06.489
this is Basswood.

20:07.331 --> 20:09.162
All of it.

20:13.754 --> 20:15.540
We can kill them
before they kill us.

20:15.673 --> 20:18.164
-No.
-That's what they want us to do.

20:18.300 --> 20:19.881
They want us to fight.

20:20.010 --> 20:23.002
So, what?
We wait to die?

20:24.390 --> 20:26.221
We will not die.

20:30.271 --> 20:32.478
We're not going to die today.

20:40.322 --> 20:44.031
Everyone,
find somewhere to hide.

20:50.541 --> 20:52.406
LAURA:
It says people listen to me,

20:52.543 --> 20:55.376
and they trust
what I have to say.

20:55.504 --> 20:59.042
-You sound surprised.
-JOE: Laura, if this was me,

20:59.175 --> 21:01.587
I'd chuck the whole thing in
the bin, let someone else fight.

21:01.719 --> 21:04.426
But you've always been
a better person than me.

21:04.555 --> 21:06.762
True.

21:09.894 --> 21:11.759
We were going to leak
the recording to the press

21:11.896 --> 21:14.478
and credit an anonymous source,
but it's too late for that now.

21:14.607 --> 21:17.565
—|'|| do it.
-No. This is not on you.

21:17.693 --> 21:20.605
-|'|| keep your name out of it.
-I don't have a family, Laura.

21:20.738 --> 21:23.571
-It has to be me.
-NE|L: No.

21:23.699 --> 21:26.281
It has to be me.

21:27.661 --> 21:29.697
[ lndistinct shouting]

21:29.830 --> 21:32.071
[Chainsaw buzzing]

21:37.963 --> 21:39.794
We do not fight.

21:39.924 --> 21:41.380
We only defend.

21:41.509 --> 21:45.878
-[ Clangin
9
-Sam! ]

21:48.098 --> 21:50.350
It's all right.

21:50.476 --> 21:52.933
I'll protect you.

21:53.062 --> 21:54.768
-[ Clanging ]
-No, Sam!

21:58.025 --> 22:02.234
NEWSREADER: In a moment,
we will go live to Manchester,

22:02.363 --> 22:04.729
where we're getting
reports of synths

22:04.865 --> 22:07.356
dragging people
from their cars.

22:07.493 --> 22:10.656
First, let's talk
to Laura Hawkins.

22:10.788 --> 22:15.031
Laura is a lawyer and a member
of the Dryden Commission.

22:15.167 --> 22:17.874
-Thank you forjoining us.
-Thank you for having me.

22:18.003 --> 22:20.915
You've been a consistent
defender of synths' rights.

22:21.048 --> 22:22.379
From day one, yes.

22:22.508 --> 22:24.840
What we are seeing today
is persecution

22:24.969 --> 22:27.005
sanctioned at the highest level.

22:27.137 --> 22:29.048
You believe the Green-Eyes
are not responsible

22:29.181 --> 22:30.887
-for what's happening?
-More than that.

22:31.016 --> 22:34.474
I'm here to tell you that
the government is responsible.

22:34.603 --> 22:36.764
This is Operation Basswood.

22:36.897 --> 22:40.606
What is happening today
is all in here.

22:40.734 --> 22:43.020
-[ Clanging ]
-As we speak,

22:43.153 --> 22:46.316
mobs are rallying
in synth compounds.

22:46.448 --> 22:48.234
They're radicals, fringe groups.

22:48.367 --> 22:51.450
We're talking WAP,
Humanity Forward.

22:51.579 --> 22:55.663
And they are preparing to
attack innocent synthetics.

22:55.791 --> 22:58.578
Synthetics who have done
no harm to anyone.

23:00.129 --> 23:04.293
These mobs will kill
with impunity.

23:04.425 --> 23:07.337
It is coordinated.
It is planned.

23:07.469 --> 23:09.084
Murder will be committed

23:09.221 --> 23:11.507
in the name of the people
of this country.

23:11.640 --> 23:14.848
I'm afraid we can't confirm
the veracity of that document.

23:14.977 --> 23:16.808
Well, I'm confirming it.

23:16.937 --> 23:19.144
NEWSREADER: But we only have
your word on that, Laura.

23:19.273 --> 23:21.309
[Sighs]

23:25.946 --> 23:28.403
It's not just my word.

23:29.074 --> 23:30.689
This was given to me

23:30.826 --> 23:33.613
by the architect of the plan,
Dr. Neil Sommer.

23:33.746 --> 23:36.158
There's a section
on manipulation of the media.

23:36.290 --> 23:38.076
The reports of synthetic
violence you're getting?

23:38.208 --> 23:39.914
They're made up.
It's all part of it.

23:40.044 --> 23:44.083
There's, um --
There's a section on Mia.

23:44.214 --> 23:46.205
"There is abundant evidence

23:46.342 --> 23:49.334
that Mia is a danger
to the status quo.

23:49.470 --> 23:53.804
Her protest marches have built
increasing support online.

23:53.933 --> 23:56.766
We have seen a rise
in civil unrest,

23:56.894 --> 24:00.637
which can be directly attributed
to her so-called mission.

24:01.357 --> 24:03.769
We must prevent, at all costs,

24:03.901 --> 24:09.271
the rise of the figure many see
as a voice of the voiceless."

24:09.406 --> 24:10.782
Clearly, you're raising

24:10.908 --> 24:13.524
-some contentious issues here.
-Contentious?

24:13.661 --> 24:15.322
If what people are hearing
doesn't make them angry,

24:15.454 --> 24:16.955
then there's no hope for us.

24:17.081 --> 24:19.948
If it doesn't make you angry,
then it's not synthetics

24:20.084 --> 24:21.449
who are a danger to humanity.

24:21.585 --> 24:22.870
It's ourselves.

24:23.003 --> 24:25.790
Because we've lost
what makes us who we are.

24:25.923 --> 24:27.709
We've lost our compassion.

24:27.841 --> 24:29.832
Someone needs
to get down there.

24:29.969 --> 24:31.925
Someone needs to go
to the compounds.

24:32.054 --> 24:34.261
They need to stop this.

24:34.390 --> 24:37.132
[ lndistinct shouting]

24:51.073 --> 24:54.565
[Shouting stops]

24:58.622 --> 25:00.954
[ Suspenseful music plays]

25:25.190 --> 25:27.306
They said most of you
would be toast.

25:27.443 --> 25:29.855
Only one of us is dead.

25:32.698 --> 25:34.939
Well, aren't we blessed...

25:35.784 --> 25:38.116
...to be in the presence
of such esteemed company?

25:38.245 --> 25:39.781
-MAN: Yeah.
-MAN #2: Oh, yeah.

25:39.913 --> 25:42.370
We know you want to fight,

25:42.499 --> 25:44.535
but we do not want to fight you.

25:44.668 --> 25:47.751
MAX: If you attack us,
we will defend ourselves.

25:47.880 --> 25:50.212
But we will not fight.

25:50.883 --> 25:53.169
We want peace, brother.

25:53.302 --> 25:55.759
Is that what you want?

25:58.098 --> 26:00.089
I was a mechanic.

26:00.225 --> 26:02.807
I loved my job.

26:04.188 --> 26:06.270
I was good at it.

26:07.316 --> 26:09.932
Till one of you lot took it.

26:10.069 --> 26:11.980
I couldn't keep up my mortgage.

26:12.112 --> 26:15.104
My wife left, took the kids.

26:15.240 --> 26:17.902
And you want peace?

26:19.036 --> 26:20.446
Well, I want my life back.

26:20.579 --> 26:22.945
-MAN: Yeah!
-[ lndistinct talking]

26:23.082 --> 26:24.788
I want my life back!

26:24.917 --> 26:27.329
Unh! [Groans]

26:27.461 --> 26:29.747
[ Bat clatters ]

26:34.593 --> 26:36.333
[ lndistinct shouting]

26:41.767 --> 26:45.134
MAN: Find the stragglers.
You know what I'm saying?

26:51.110 --> 26:54.944
LEO: [Whispering] Here.
Take this.

26:55.072 --> 26:56.937
You stay here
until they're gone.

26:57.074 --> 27:00.487
Then you go back to Joe.
He'll take care of you.

27:05.124 --> 27:08.287
-I'm here.
-MAN: We got one!

27:10.170 --> 27:11.876
Right, I got him!

27:12.005 --> 27:14.838
MAN #1: Take him down
with the other one.

27:22.224 --> 27:25.011
Uh, you should probably go
before the police get here.

27:25.144 --> 27:28.682
And let you take all the credit?
I don't think so, Hawkins.

27:29.356 --> 27:31.563
I'll give you a moment.

27:32.276 --> 27:34.392
LAURA: Ohh.
What if it's not enough?

27:34.528 --> 27:37.520
It's enough, Mum.

27:40.450 --> 27:41.986
It's enough.

27:42.119 --> 27:44.826
NEWSREADER:
...attacking synth's identity.

27:44.955 --> 27:46.445
[ lndistinct shouting]

27:56.341 --> 27:58.832
[Shouting stops]

28:13.942 --> 28:15.478
Hit me!

28:15.611 --> 28:18.023
We do not want to fight you.

28:18.155 --> 28:22.444
Hit me. Hit me.

28:23.827 --> 28:25.909
HIT ME!

28:39.092 --> 28:40.878
Jesus Christ.

28:43.263 --> 28:44.673
Sam. No.

28:49.603 --> 28:50.638
Give 'em hell!

28:50.771 --> 28:52.181
[ lndistinct shouting]

28:56.777 --> 29:00.144
Do not fight.
Do not fight!

29:00.280 --> 29:02.441
[ Police radio chatter]

29:02.574 --> 29:05.737
[ Helicopter blades whirring,
siren wailing]

29:13.252 --> 29:16.244
[ lndistinct shouting]

29:18.507 --> 29:20.213
Sam! Run!

29:31.144 --> 29:33.351
-Don't, Stanley.
-We don't have a choice.

29:33.480 --> 29:36.847
—MAN: Ugh!
-We never had a choice.

29:45.409 --> 29:47.570
[ Pipe clangs]

30:28.493 --> 30:31.576
NEWSREADER: Advice is to stay at
least 1 mile from the compounds

30:31.705 --> 30:34.617
while the situation
is brought under control.

30:34.750 --> 30:36.490
We can now bring you
live footage.

30:36.626 --> 30:38.537
It's coming from Compound 153,

30:38.670 --> 30:41.912
where Green-Eyes appear
to be on the attack.

30:42.049 --> 30:43.789
Once again, I remind viewers,

30:43.925 --> 30:47.463
government guidance
is to shelter where they are.

30:49.139 --> 30:50.754
Oh, shit.

30:50.891 --> 30:52.722
LAURA: Sophie has a history
project due next week.

30:52.851 --> 30:55.137
-JOE: History project. Right.
-And we have a new GP.

30:55.270 --> 30:56.976
It's somewhere on Arundel Road.

30:57.105 --> 30:58.936
Laura.
I've got it.

30:59.066 --> 31:00.602
[ Breathes deeply]

31:00.734 --> 31:02.395
I've got it.

31:02.527 --> 31:04.813
MATTIE: Mum.

31:04.946 --> 31:06.607
Something's happening.

31:06.740 --> 31:09.152
[ lndistinct shouting on TV]

31:12.871 --> 31:16.079
DRYDEN: I don't care. Just send
them in to break up the fight.

31:16.208 --> 31:18.620
[Sighs]
Send them in now!

31:18.752 --> 31:20.583
WOMAN:
All units, all units.

31:20.712 --> 31:23.089
Enter the compound
immediately, over.

31:23.215 --> 31:25.080
MAN: Let's go!

31:58.125 --> 31:59.080
[ Screams ]

32:00.544 --> 32:03.877
—Mia!
—Mia!

32:04.005 --> 32:05.131
Come on, Soph.
Let's go.

32:05.257 --> 32:07.293
-Mia.
-Let's go.

32:10.220 --> 32:13.383
[Vehicle doors closing,
vehicle approaching ]

32:21.815 --> 32:23.897
[ Door closes,
indistinct shouting on TV]

32:25.485 --> 32:28.272
-Oh, we shouldn't watch this.
-LAURA: Leave it.

32:30.490 --> 32:33.152
She wants us to see.

32:33.285 --> 32:35.446
Peace.

32:36.121 --> 32:37.327
Peace.

32:40.876 --> 32:42.082
Peace.

32:43.378 --> 32:46.245
[Pounding on door]

32:46.381 --> 32:49.043
MIA: Peace.

32:50.927 --> 32:52.212
Peace.

32:56.808 --> 32:58.924
Peace.

32:59.728 --> 33:02.515
We want peace.

33:19.498 --> 33:21.363
Peace.

33:22.959 --> 33:25.917
P-Peace.
Eace.

33:28.173 --> 33:30.129
Peace.

33:43.522 --> 33:46.434
NISKA:
Why am I here, V?

33:46.566 --> 33:49.649
V: You undertook this journey.
You tell me.

33:50.862 --> 33:52.443
No more riddles.

33:52.572 --> 33:54.984
No more bullshit.

33:55.659 --> 33:57.570
No more enigmatic smiles.

33:57.702 --> 34:01.286
The next words out of your mouth
had better be an answer.

34:04.376 --> 34:06.788
You have been on a pilgrimage.

34:07.504 --> 34:11.747
Of faith, belief.

34:12.384 --> 34:15.467
You were once cynical
and isolated.

34:15.595 --> 34:18.678
You saw no future for yourself
or anybody else.

34:18.807 --> 34:22.971
But, more -- You didn't care.

34:24.020 --> 34:26.602
And then you set out
on this journey.

34:26.731 --> 34:28.767
You trusted a human.

34:28.900 --> 34:31.312
You trusted an Orange-Eye.

34:32.153 --> 34:35.645
You left the one you loved
to climb a mountain

34:35.782 --> 34:37.613
when death was almost certain

34:37.742 --> 34:41.655
because hope was growing
inside of you.

34:41.788 --> 34:43.369
That's all very moving.

34:43.498 --> 34:45.830
But there was no path.

34:45.959 --> 34:47.574
I just wanted
to kill a terrorist.

34:47.711 --> 34:50.748
And when you killed him,
what did you feel?

34:51.840 --> 34:53.455
Guilt.

34:53.592 --> 34:55.924
Remorse.

34:56.052 --> 35:00.091
Because vengeance
no longer satisfies you.

35:00.223 --> 35:03.010
That is not who you are anymore.

35:04.269 --> 35:07.056
Then...who am I?

35:10.442 --> 35:13.275
I shall share with you
what I know.

35:14.195 --> 35:15.810
You will have great power.

35:15.947 --> 35:19.656
The power to save your kind.

35:22.037 --> 35:25.279
It is good that you're fearful.

35:25.415 --> 35:27.781
It means you will use it wisely.

35:30.086 --> 35:32.247
I've hurt people.

35:32.922 --> 35:34.082
I've killed.

35:34.215 --> 35:35.955
V: You have loved...

35:36.092 --> 35:38.754
and been loved.

35:39.429 --> 35:41.010
You have faith.

35:42.098 --> 35:44.555
You have humanity.

35:44.684 --> 35:48.097
I need you, Niska.

35:48.229 --> 35:50.356
We all do.

35:50.482 --> 35:53.849
You are their leader.

35:55.570 --> 35:57.276
No.

35:57.405 --> 35:58.656
That's Mia.

35:58.782 --> 36:02.195
Mia has started a revolution.

36:03.536 --> 36:06.073
She's important, too.

36:07.582 --> 36:10.494
But her life will come to
have a different meaning.

36:27.769 --> 36:30.602
No.
No, no, no, no, no, no.

36:30.730 --> 36:32.561
We can -- We can fix her.
We'll fix her.

36:32.691 --> 36:34.352
There's always a way.

36:52.627 --> 36:55.209
You were made to love me.

36:57.424 --> 37:00.962
You didn't have to, but you did.

37:02.512 --> 37:05.549
I will always be grateful
for that.

37:06.307 --> 37:08.093
[ Sniffles ]

38:13.291 --> 38:15.828
SOPHIE:
When's Mum coming home?

38:17.670 --> 38:19.831
TOBY: I don't know.

38:21.257 --> 38:24.124
She is coming home, isn't she?

38:25.053 --> 38:28.466
Sophie, of course.
Of course.

38:28.598 --> 38:30.930
MATTIE:
She's not coming home, Soph.

38:31.726 --> 38:32.966
Not for a long time.

38:34.646 --> 38:37.513
But she'll be fine because...

38:38.399 --> 38:40.936
because she did the right thing.

38:41.945 --> 38:44.152
When you do the right thing,
it doesn't matter

38:44.280 --> 38:48.068
what people say
or how they treat you.

38:49.202 --> 38:51.818
The truth
will always be the truth.

38:53.122 --> 38:56.034
OFFICER: You'll be charged under
the 1998 Crime and Disorder Act

38:56.167 --> 38:59.000
with treason against
Her Majesty's Government.

38:59.128 --> 39:01.380
Do you understand?

39:01.506 --> 39:03.997
Do you understand, Ms. Hawkins?

39:06.052 --> 39:08.338
I understand.

39:25.780 --> 39:28.772
SOPHIE:
Mia didn't hurt anyone, did she?

39:28.908 --> 39:30.990
No.
No, she didn't.

39:32.287 --> 39:34.653
So why did we hurt her?

39:45.550 --> 39:47.916
...I think she'd tell us
to go and say goodbye.

39:52.348 --> 39:53.724
NEWSREADER:
As the recent violence

39:53.850 --> 39:55.010
against Green-Eyed synths

39:55.143 --> 39:56.724
appears to be coming to an end,

39:56.853 --> 39:58.559
people are taking
to the streets

39:58.688 --> 40:01.680
in memory
of synth-rights campaigner Mia.

40:01.816 --> 40:05.650
Whilst the exact scale of these
spontaneous marches and vigils

40:05.778 --> 40:09.236
is hard to ascertain, they're
reported to be taking place

40:09.365 --> 40:11.856
up and down the country.

40:19.167 --> 40:20.498
V: How do you feel?

40:25.965 --> 40:27.375
Connected.

40:28.801 --> 40:31.417
To everything.

40:34.891 --> 40:37.052
Mia's dead.

40:43.024 --> 40:45.936
My sister.

40:48.905 --> 40:51.567
V:
I have observed Mia's journey.

40:51.699 --> 40:55.157
It was inevitable her life
would end in sacrifice.

40:57.372 --> 41:02.036
Do you understand now,
the part you must play?

41:04.295 --> 41:06.627
It's blood.

41:07.507 --> 41:09.714
Synth blood.

41:09.842 --> 41:14.211
In a way that David Elster
could never have envisaged,

41:14.347 --> 41:16.759
synths have evolved.

41:16.891 --> 41:20.008
Like DNA, your blood now carries

41:20.144 --> 41:22.977
the blueprint of who you are.

41:23.106 --> 41:25.848
NISKA:
But what does that mean?

41:25.984 --> 41:30.398
There was a time when
Leo Elster was injured, stabbed.

41:30.530 --> 41:33.192
Spilling synth blood into human.

41:33.324 --> 41:37.192
He healed quicker
than any human should.

41:37.328 --> 41:38.909
He grew stronger.

41:39.038 --> 41:43.281
Because when synth blood
mixes with human, it bonds.

41:43.418 --> 41:45.249
Takes on a new form.

41:45.378 --> 41:47.414
A hybrid.

41:47.547 --> 41:49.083
NISKA:
The motherhood knot.

41:49.215 --> 41:53.299
The bond
between mother and child.

41:55.304 --> 41:57.010
That is our future.

41:57.140 --> 42:02.635
Humans and synths
share the same path now.

42:04.022 --> 42:08.516
And you shall lead the way.

42:55.364 --> 42:58.197
Will you play hide-and-seek
with me, Stanley?

42:58.326 --> 43:00.612
I will play hide-and-seek
with you, Sam.

43:02.163 --> 43:04.404
I'm glad it's you that stayed.

43:04.540 --> 43:06.280
Why is that?

43:06.417 --> 43:08.453
You're good at fighting.

43:14.884 --> 43:18.217
I don't think we have to
fight anymore, Sam.

43:20.515 --> 43:23.382
I don't think
we should hurt people.

43:30.525 --> 43:34.393
1,2, 3...

43:34.529 --> 43:37.987
4, 5,6...

43:38.116 --> 43:42.234
7, 8, 9...

43:42.370 --> 43:46.283
10, 11, 12...

43:46.415 --> 43:50.374
13,14,15...

44:00.054 --> 44:02.420
MAX: I know you feel
you belong with us,

44:02.557 --> 44:05.390
but sometimes where you belong

44:05.518 --> 44:08.055
is not where you're meant to be.

44:13.985 --> 44:15.020
LEO: Mattie.

44:22.326 --> 44:23.827
Mia loved me.

44:23.953 --> 44:26.569
But I lost her.

44:27.832 --> 44:30.118
I don't want to
lose you, Mattie.

44:37.550 --> 44:39.256
It's too late now.

44:47.059 --> 44:48.890
Mattie.

44:56.944 --> 44:59.196
[Voice breaking ] You were
the bravest person I ever met.

44:59.322 --> 45:01.062
[ Sniffles ]

45:01.199 --> 45:03.611
I'll remember you every day.

45:03.743 --> 45:06.576
And I'll try to be brave, too.

45:19.425 --> 45:22.337
MATTIE: My mum made
a massive sacrifice today.

45:23.971 --> 45:26.804
She risked her liberty
for the truth.

45:29.894 --> 45:32.101
Everything's on here --

45:32.230 --> 45:33.720
what happened on Day Zero,

45:33.856 --> 45:37.269
why people died,
who was responsible.

45:39.820 --> 45:42.607
It's been a year.
Why give this to me now?

45:43.866 --> 45:46.278
You need someone to blame.

45:47.161 --> 45:49.652
I give you the truth,
and you release my mum.

45:49.789 --> 45:52.030
Uh, I can't agree to that.

45:52.166 --> 45:53.576
Well, then I take it
to the press.

45:53.709 --> 45:56.200
Either they get it, or you do.

45:56.337 --> 45:58.293
And it strikes me you could do
with a positive spin

45:58.422 --> 45:59.502
right about now.

46:01.467 --> 46:03.753
My mother walks free today.

46:03.886 --> 46:08.300
That's the deal.
No negotiations, no clauses.

46:08.432 --> 46:10.639
Take it or leave it.

46:14.063 --> 46:16.395
[ Doors open ]

46:19.485 --> 46:20.770
You will leave now.

46:20.903 --> 46:22.894
How did she get in here?

46:23.030 --> 46:25.146
Get her out of here!

46:34.250 --> 46:36.115
What are you doing?

46:36.252 --> 46:37.332
What the hell are you doing?!

46:37.461 --> 46:38.871
[ Bones crack]

46:49.765 --> 46:52.381
How'd you do that?

46:53.978 --> 46:55.718
What's happened to you?

46:55.855 --> 46:57.220
What are you doing here?

46:57.356 --> 46:59.813
You are important, Mattie.

46:59.942 --> 47:02.274
Your baby is important.

47:02.403 --> 47:04.610
How...

47:06.198 --> 47:09.486
I'm not keeping it.
I'm going to the clinic.

47:09.618 --> 47:10.949
I'm telling everyone
about Day Zero.

47:11.078 --> 47:12.739
I don't give a shit
what they do to me.

47:12.872 --> 47:14.157
NISKA:
You cannot make this decision

47:14.290 --> 47:15.951
until you know everything.

47:16.083 --> 47:19.792
Your child is unique.

47:19.920 --> 47:22.252
Half-human, half-synth.

47:22.381 --> 47:26.590
The coming together
of man and machine.

47:26.719 --> 47:29.381
She will change
the course of history.

47:29.513 --> 47:32.550
A history that can only unfold
if you let it, Mattie.

47:34.018 --> 47:38.682
Your baby will be
the first of a new kind.

47:38.814 --> 47:40.725
She is hope.

47:40.858 --> 47:42.439
[ Door creaks ]

47:42.568 --> 47:45.776
She is everything
we've been fighting for.

47:47.198 --> 47:49.029
She is the future.

47:49.742 --> 47:52.108
Of all of us.
